Every year during Pride Month, I do some sort of gratitude post to recognize and thank all of the LQBTQ+ community who made it possible for my wife and I to live openly. We’ve been together over 30 years and when we first started secretly dating, things were very different. We never dreamed of a world where we could be legally married. 
.
We realize those rights are not inalienable and we aren’t naive. We know a lot of people wish we’d go back to the closet we came from. But for the bad asses who fought and still fight to let us out, from our family to yours, we say THANK YOU a million times. 
.
We don’t feel like we are less human than straight people and we are so grateful that there are so many allies who feel the same. We’ve stood for love for over 30 years and thank all of those who stand with us. If it weren’t for the strength of many, we know our life would look very different. Love to all!
.
And before you ask, YES, this @monicavinader Freedom Bracelet is still for sale on their website. (Thanks Monica!) 😉
.
#loveislove #pridemonth #equalrightsforall #monicavinader #pride

This beautiful human next to me was my sister Kim. She was the best sister any person could ever hope for. We lost her on Saturday after a 13 year battle with Ovarian Cancer (which never stopped her for a moment of living every day like it was her last.). She was filled with faith, love, joy and happiness.  I’m the luckiest sister in the world and am so grateful to have gotten to be part of your life. The amount of love you had in your life is a testament to your goodness. Love you always. ❤️

I was gifted this by @ourselfskin but I can PROMISE you that this is the BEST eye product I’ve ever used. The holy grail of line diminishing goodness. I cannot overstate this. If you can get it, I 10000% recommend you do. It’s THAT good. I wish you could also hear the tone of my voice trying to emphatically tell you how good it is. I’m about to be 52 and the lines around my eyes look SO MUCH better. And my eye lids look better. Just can’t speak highly enough. 
#eyecream #eyeserum #matureskin #skincareroutine #holygrail

Kim wasn’t able to personally respond to the generous outpouring of love in her final weeks, but asked that we reach out to all who expressed their friendship, care and beautiful messages.  She felt surrounded by love and prayer, which provided immense comfort. 

We want to invite all who loved her to please join us in remembrance: 

Services will be held Friday, October 20th at 11am at Highland Park United Methodist Church in the Sanctuary immediately followed by a reception in the Great Hall. 

Please join us as we remember Kim.  Our family requests everyone wear brightly colored attire in remembrance of Kim’s joy.
